They like skiing.
- Oni lubią jazdę na nartach.
Skiing is their favourite sport.
- Narciarstwo to ich ulubiony sport.

Przyrostek -ing służy do tworzenia rzeczowników odczasownikowych, czyli nazw czynności.
Np. I like swimming. - Lubię pływanie.

Czasowników z końcówką -ing używamy
a) jako rzeczowników.
Np. Exercising is good for your health. - Gimnastykowanie się jest zdrowe.
b) po czasownikach:
like - lubic,
dislike - nie lubić,
hate - nie cierpieć, nienawidzić,
enjoy - dobrze się bawić,
prefer - woleć,
stop - przestać,
finish - przestać, skończyć,
start - zacząć,
begin - zacząć.
Np. She stopped talking. - Przestała mówić.

c) po przyimkach
Np. I'm thinking of going to Italy - Zastanawiam się nad wyjazdem do Włoch.

d) w wyrażeniach z czasownikiem go.
Np. She went shopping yesterday - Ona wybrała się wczoraj na zakupy.

Uwaga: Konstrukcji like/love + -ing używamy mówiąc ogólnie, że lubimy cos robić.
Np. I love travelling. - Lubię podróżować.
Konstrukcji would like/love + bezokolicznik z to używamy, by powiedzieć, że chcemy coś zrobić (jednorazowo).
Np. I would like to travel to China one day - Chciałbym kiedyś pojechać do Chin.

cwiczenie 8
wstaw podane w nawiasach czasowniki w bezokoliczniku lub z koncowka ing.
1 Juliet enjoys [...] (play) the guitar.
2 He started [...] (drive) when he was 17 years old.
3 I wanted [...] (take) my dog to the park yesterday.
4 I can't [...] (travel) to Australia alone.
5 He likes [...] (do) jigsaw puzzles.
6 Philip agreed [...] (paint) the garden fence.
7 I finished [...] (eat) breakfast an hour ago.
8 Fiona hopes [...] (buy) a new car soon.
9 Can Sam [...] (do) jigsaw puzzles.
10 I put the shopping away before [...] (cook) dinner.
1 playing
2 driving 5 doing
3 to take 6 to paint
4 travel 7 eating
8 to buy
9 do
10 cooking

cwiczenie 9
wstaw podane w nawiasach czasowniki w bezokoliczniku lub z koncowka ing.
A: Where are you going? It's too cold 1) [...] (go) out today.
B: I must 2) [...] (buy) some stamps because I want 3) [...] (post) some letters.
I'll wear my coat so I'll be warm enough
A: I will 4) [...] (come) with you.
B: All right. I also want 5) [...] (visit) Aunt Milly this morning, but I won't 6) [...] (stay) too long.
A: Good. I like 7) [...] (talk) to her and she enjoys 8) [...] (tell) us stories about her past.
B: Oh no, I forgot! Aunt Milly goes 9) [...] (shop) every Saturday morning.
A: It doesn't matter. We like 10) [...] (buy) things too, so we can 11) [...] (go) with her.
B: That's a good idea. I would like 12) [...] (do) that. I've got enough time before I start work this afternoon.
1 to go
2 buy 6 stay 10 buying
3 to post 7 talking 11 go
4 come 8 telling 12 to do
5 to visit 9 shopping

cwiczenie 10
uzupelnij zdania wpisujac czasowniki z listy w bezokoliczniku lub z koncowka ing.
wear, help, buy, become, be, play,
go, take, say, watch, cook, speak

1 I love animals. I'm thinking of [...] a vet.
2 Steve likes [...] sunglasses, even in winter.
3 Would you like [...] television?
4 Pamela asked me [...] her with her homework.
5 You must [...] the dog for a walk every day.
6 Paul left without [...] goodbye last night.
7 I went to the butcher's [...] some meat for dinner.
8 Fred enjoys [...]. He wants to be a chef.
9 What shall we do today? I would love [...] for a walk.
10 I want [...] an astronaut when I grow up.
11 "Why do you want to go to the park?" "I want [...] with my friends."
12 James is very clever. He can [...] four languages.
1 becoming
2 wearing 8 cooking
3 to watch 9 to go
4 to help 10 to be
5 take 11 to play
6 saying 12 speak
7 to buy

cwiczenie 11
uzupelnij dialogi podanymi czasownikami w bezokoliczniku lub z koncowka ing.
A: What do you want 1) [...] (do) today?
B: I'm thinking of 2) [...] (go) to the park for a picnic. Do you want 3) [...] (come)?
A Yes, please. It's a lovely day for a picnic.

A: I enjoy 4)[...] (go) on picnics, don't you, Frank?
B: Yes, and I love 5) [...] (sit) in the park.
A: What's this? Oh no, it has started 6) [...] (rain).
B: Let's 7) [...] (put) everything back in the car.

A: What shall we 8) [...] (do) now?
B: Would you like 9) [...] (see) a film?
A: Not really. How about 10) [...](spend) the
evening at my house?

A: I'll 11) [...] (make) us some tea.
B: Thank you, I would 12) [...] (love) some.
What a day!
1 to do
2 going 8 do
3 to come 9 to see
4 going 10 spending
5 sitting 11 make
6 raining 12 love
7 put